name:
High Hopes
You Were The Future
PRE-ORDER
description:
Fair Ohs own Joe Ryan returns in his High Hopes guise with a full album after last year’s 5 track EP. Mixing his love for 80’s Soul music, songs of heartbreak and weird offbeat chops makes for listening unlike anyone one else right now. Imagine a baritone Ariel Pink playing dark electronic soul music!

name:

EP
PRE-ORDER DEC 2013
description:
In December we have the debut release for London’s Withcing Waves who feature a member of Suplex alumni Weird Menace and one of the Soundsaver’s team who have recorded a ton of the bands who Suplex have released. This duo is perfect for fans of The Warmers and other late 90’s Dischord bands.

name:
El Duque
Cuatro Canciones Para La Paz Mundial EP
SUP #22
description:
A solo EP from the one and only E.B.Frankel of Fair Ohs fame. Channeling the mind of Santana, the body of John McLaughlin and the spirit of Jimmy Hendrix, this extended play of beautiful rolling guitars is only backed by the sounds of nature, French television talk shows and travels in Morocco.

This is the psych odyssey 2013 has been waiting for and 2014 needs.

Tracklisting -

Aguas Negras Despedezar
Generador de Olas
Tempestad
Hinduista
